'''Every Disabled Child Matters (EDCM)''' is a [[political campaign]] based in England with the aim of improving rights for disabled children and their families. The stated campaign objectives<ref>[http://www.edcm.org.uk Every Disabled Child Matters website]</ref> focus on issues such as [[poverty]], [[education]], access to [[Her Majesty's Government|government]] [[Public services|services]] and [[Inclusion (disability rights)|inclusion]]. The campaign was launched in September 2006. == Running and strategy == The campaign is run jointly by four organisations: * [[Contact a Family]] * Council for Disabled Children ( part of [[National Children's Bureau]] ) * [[Mencap]] * Special Education Consortium (part of [[National Children's Bureau]] ) The strategy for the campaign is set by an executive team drawn from these four organisations.
== References == {{reflist}}
[[Category:Disability rights organizations]] [[Category:Disability organisations based in England]] [[Category:Politics of England]] [[Category:Political campaigns in the United Kingdom]] [[Category:Poverty in England]] [[Category:Education in England]] [[Category:Governance of England]]
{{England-org-stub}} {{England-poli-stub}} {{poli-org-stub}}

The '''First Circuit Court''' of the '''[[Supreme People's Court]]''' of the [[People's Republic of China]] (中华人民共和国最高人民法院第一巡回法庭), is a [[circuit court]] created in December 2014 and opened on January 28, 2015, in [[Shenzhen]], China. It has jurisdiction in the provinces of [[Guangdong]], [[Guangxi]], and [[Hainan]].<ref>[http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/china/2015-02/05/c_133973171.htm China's first circuit courts in full operations]</ref><ref name="xinhua1">[http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/china/2015-01/28/c_133953979.htm China's first circuit court established in Shenzhen]</ref>

Differing from a circuit court in a [[common law]] jurisdiction, the First Circuit is part of a pilot program to establish circuit courts of the Supreme People's Court outside [[Beijing]], the seat of the national government, with the same level of jurisdiction of the supreme court, i.e. cases decided by the circuit courts are deemed as finally decided by the supreme court itself.<ref name="xinhua1" /> The pilot program is carried out in an effort to avoid local influences.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-01-28/china-s-to-open-first-circuit-court-in-shenzhen-next-week China Will Open First Circuit Court in Shenzhen Next Week]</ref>

