{{Other uses|German Party (disambiguation){{!}}German Party}}
{{unref|date=October 2011}} The '''German Party''' ({{lang-de|Partei der Deutschen}}) was a political party of [[Germans]] in the [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]]. The party was formed in 1922 and participated in elections until it was banned following [[Yugoslavs|Yugoslav]] king [[Alexander I of Yugoslavia|Alexander I]]'s dictatorship of January 6, 1929.
==Performance by election== *[[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes parliamentary election, 1923|1923]] - 43,415 votes, 8 of 312 seats *[[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes parliamentary election, 1925|1925]] - 45,117 votes, 5 of 315 seats *[[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes parliamentary election, 1927|1927]] - 49,849 votes, 6 of 315 seats
